    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Hey there! \ud83d\ude97 I\u2019m parting ways with my absolute pride and joy. This beauty is in pristine condition\u2014honestly, it still looks and smells like it just rolled off the lot! I\u2019ve babied this car since day one, keeping it garage-kept and professionally detailed. It drives like a total dream and is ready for its next adventure. If you're looking for perfection without the brand-new price tag, this is the one! Feel free to reach out with any questions!",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 21
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Offered is a concours-level 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, a definitive example of the 996.2 wide-body silhouette. This specimen features the M96/03 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six, exhibiting optimal compression across all cylinders and zero evidence of bore scoring. The mechanical provenance is exhaustive, headlined by a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a proactive rear main seal replacement. Power is delivered through a G96/31 6-speed manual transaxle to the factory viscous-clutch all-wheel-drive system. The chassis retains its factory-spec rigidity, equipped with Porsche Stability Management (PSM) and four-piston monobloc calipers over cross-drilled vented rotors. The Arctic Silver Metallic finish shows no signs of road rash or clear coat failure, while the interior leather maintains its original matte texture, free from UV damage or bolster wear. This is a turn-key, investment-grade vehicle for the discerning air-cooled or water-cooled purist.",
      "price": 47500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 21
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Used car in mint condition. Garage kept. No accidents. Clean title. Full service history included. Inspections welcome.",
      "price": 43500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 21
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Presenting a truly showroom-grade vehicle that stands as a testament to meticulous ownership. The exterior is finished in a deep, lustrous coat that has been professionally ceramic-coated, showing absolutely no rock chips, swirl marks, or blemishes. It has been strictly garage-kept and protected from the elements since day one. Inside, the cabin is indistinguishable from new; the premium leather upholstery remains supple with no bolster wear, the carpets are spotless, and it retains that distinct new-car scent. Every technological feature, from the infotainment system to the climate control, operates with precision. Mechanically, the car is in peak form, backed by a comprehensive service history performed exclusively by certified technicians. This is a rare opportunity to own a collector-quality vehicle that offers a driving experience identical to the day it was first delivered.",
